1) Virtual Environments
- If you want update and extral packages you can install them by
  setting up a virtual environment:
setup v2014.10.29 anaconda
conda create -n my_anaconda --clone=/nerc/packages/anaconda/v2014.10.29/anaconda
--
Bash:
source activate my_anaconda # In bash shell, add to .bashrc
                              you're done!
--
CSH (nocs default):
source ~/.conda/envs/bin/activate my_anaconda 

add to .cshrc
source ~/.conda/envs/bin/activate my_anaconda
setenv PATH "/noc/users/${USER}/.conda/envs/my_root/bin:${PATH}"
--
You will need to restart any notebooks for this to take effect!

You can now:
conda install <package>
pip install <package>
conda update <package>

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
2) No screen
You can run a notebook server fully in the background:

ipython notebook --profile=<profilename> ~/output.txt &

now this will be hard to kill so you need to know this command:

ps fe -u $USER 

This will list all your processes to kill one of them:

kill -9 <process ID>

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
